# chain — LangGraph AI Pipeline

This is `movie-finder-chain` (`backend/chain/`) — the core intelligence layer of Movie Finder.
GitHub repo: `aharbii/movie-finder-chain` · Parent: `aharbii/movie-finder-backend` · Tracker: `aharbii/movie-finder`

## What this submodule does

LangGraph 8-node pipeline that classifies user input, searches Qdrant, enriches via IMDb, and answers with Claude.

**Pipeline flow:**
`classify` → `search_rag` → `enrich_imdb` → `reason` → `route` → `refine` / `confirm` / `answer`

## Key source layout

```
src/chain/
├── config.py       # Pydantic BaseSettings — all env vars here
├── graph.py        # LangGraph Pregel graph — node wiring
├── state.py        # MovieFinderState TypedDict
├── models/         # Domain data structures
├── nodes/          # Pure function node implementations
├── prompts/        # LLM prompt templates
├── rag/            # Qdrant vector search wrapper
└── utils/
```

## Stack

- Python 3.13, `uv` workspace member of `backend/`
- LangGraph 0.2+, LangChain 0.3+
- Models: Claude Haiku (classify), Claude Sonnet (reason / confirm / Q&A)
- Embeddings: OpenAI `text-embedding-3-large` (3072-dim — must match ingestion)
- Vector store: Qdrant Cloud (always external)
- IMDb enrichment: `imdbapi/` path dependency
- Tracing: LangSmith (opt-in via `LANGSMITH_TRACING=true`)
- Max refinements: 3 (`MAX_REFINEMENTS`)

## Quality checks (from `backend/`)

```bash
make lint && make typecheck && make test
```

## Non-negotiables

- New behaviour = new node or edge — never branch inside an existing node
- New LLM/embedding provider = new Strategy class — no `if provider ==` branching
- `MovieFinderState` fields are shared across all nodes — changes affect the whole pipeline
- Never `git add -A`, never `--no-verify`, Conventional Commits

